// express js request and response objects are the parametres of callback function used in express apps

// express request represents the http requests and has properties of request query string , parametres ,body, http header etc

//req.app => it is used to hold the reference to the instance of the express app using the middleware

// some of request object methods

//1.req.accept(types)

/* this method is used to check whether the specified content types are accepted , based on the request's accept http header field

2.req.get(field)

it returns the specified http request header field

3.req.is(type)


this method returns true if the incoming request's content type http header file matches with mime type specified by the type parameter



*/